18 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "collateral action" means an
19 action or proceeding, including an administrative proceeding, that
20 is factually or legally related to an arrest, a criminal charge, or a
21 conviction. The term includes a proceeding or action concerning a
22 seizure, a civil forfeiture, and a petition for specialized driving
23 privileges.
24 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "conviction records" means all
25 records relating to or created in connection with a conviction,
26 including a collateral action.
27 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, a "Level 6 felony" includes:
28 (1) a Class D felony (for an offense committed before July 1,
29 2014); and
30 (2) an Indiana offense punishable by an indeterminate
31 sentence under a law other than IC 35-50, if the offense is a
32 Level 6 felony at the time the person files the petition for
33 expungement.
34 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "misdemeanor" includes:
35 (1) a Class D felony (for a crime committed before July 1,
36 2014) or a Level 6 felony (for a crime committed after June
37 30, 2014), that is reduced to a misdemeanor pursuant to
38 IC 35-38-1-1.5 or IC 35-50-2-7; and
39 (2) an Indiana offense punishable by an indeterminate
40 sentence under a law other than IC 35-50, if the offense is a
41 misdemeanor at the time the person files the petition for
42 expungement.
